Antonio PIANEZZA, Appellant, v. John R. NORTHRUP, as Acting Divisional Director of Immigration and Naturalization Service, Appellee. No. 7210. Circuit Court of Appeals, Sixth Circuit. April 14, 1936. Blase- A. Buonpane and John B. Os-mun, both of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellant. E. B. Freed, U. S. Atty., of Cleveland, Ohio, for appellee.

Before MOORMAN, SIMONS, and ALLEN, Circuit Judges.

MOORMAN, Circuit Judge.

Affirmed on authority of Philippides v. Day, 283 U.S. 48, 51 S.Ct. 358, 75 L.Ed. 833, and United States v. Vanbiervliet, 284 U.S. 590, 52 S.Ct. 132, 76 L.Ed. 509.
